<subSubSection id="C34065156325FFDFFF12FE65FEADFD23" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6325FFDFFF12FE65FB2CFDF7" blockId="20.[151,1437,402,717]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6325FFDFFF12FE65FE8AFE43" bold="true" box="[151,269,403,429]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6325FFDFFE90FE65FE28FE43" author="Hagen, Y." box="[277,431,402,429]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refId="ref14785" refString="Hagen, Y. (1952) Birds of Tristan da Cunha. In: Results of the Norwegian scientific expedition to Tristan da Cunha 1937 - 1938. Vol. 20. Det Norske Videnskaps-Akademi, Oslo, pp. 1 - 248." type="book" year="1952">Hagen (1952)</bibRefCitation>
based his description of this new subspecies on 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176325FFDFFC4AFE65FBB0FE43" box="[975,1079,403,429]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="adult">one adult</specimenCount>
female, which he designated as the 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6325FFDFFF45FE41FE8FFE3F" box="[192,264,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">‘Type’</emphasis>
, and 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176325FFDFFEC1FE41FE67FE3F" box="[324,480,439,465]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="immature">two immature</specimenCount>
specimens of unknown sex. The adult female is, therefore, considered to be the 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C6325FFDFFAE4FE41FF40FE1B" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">holotype</typeStatus>
of this taxon, according to article 73.1.1 of the Code (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6325FFDFFCA9FE2DFF54FDF7" author="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refId="ref14975" refString="International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature (1999) International code of zoological nomenclature. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature 1999</bibRefCitation>
), and the immature specimens 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C6325FFDFFDA8FE09FD1BFDF7" box="[557,668,511,537]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">paratypes</typeStatus>
. All types are present in the NHMO collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6325FFDFFF42FDD5FE4EFD6B" blockId="20.[151,1437,402,717]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
All 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176325FFDFFF74FDD5FE24FDD3" box="[241,419,547,573]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
are labelled with metal tags having the collector’s field number embossed into them (
<figureCitation id="13612A1B6325FFDFFAD4FDD5FF20FD8F" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1140,1164]" captionTargetBox="[156,1427,747,1109]" captionTargetId="figure-221@20.[148,1439,741,1117]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Labels (metal tags) of type specimens in the NHMO Bird Collection of Nesospiza wilkinsi dunnei Hagen, 1952 (all collector’s labels). a) NHMO-BI-100346; b) NHMO-BI-64842; c) NHMO-BI-100347." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626781/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Figure 7</figureCitation>
). The adult female and one of the immatures were originally preserved in formalin (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6325FFDFFBC1FDB1FB4AFD8F" author="Hagen, Y." box="[1092,1229,582,609]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refId="ref14785" refString="Hagen, Y. (1952) Birds of Tristan da Cunha. In: Results of the Norwegian scientific expedition to Tristan da Cunha 1937 - 1938. Vol. 20. Det Norske Videnskaps-Akademi, Oslo, pp. 1 - 248." type="book" year="1952">Hagen 1952</bibRefCitation>
) but has later been transferred to 70% ethanol.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6325FFDFFF42FD79FEADFD23" blockId="20.[151,1437,402,717]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
The subspecies has subsequently been transferred to the congeneric 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6325FFDFFC41FD79FBC3FD47" authorityName="Cabanis" authorityYear="1873" box="[964,1092,655,681]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Nesospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acunhae">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6325FFDFFC41FD79FBC3FD47" box="[964,1092,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">N. acunhae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6325FFDFFBF4FD79FEA1FD23" authority="(Ryan 2008)" baseAuthorityName="Ryan" baseAuthorityYear="2008" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Nesospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="acunhae" subSpecies="dunnei">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6325FFDFFBF4FD79FA1BFD47" box="[1137,1436,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Nesospiza acunhae dunnei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6325FFDFFF1AFD45FE99FD23" author="Ryan, P. G." box="[159,286,691,717]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" pagination="20 - 29" refId="ref16191" refString="Ryan, P. G. (2008) Taxonomic and conservation implications of ecological speciation in Nesospiza buntings on Tristan da Cunha. Bird Conservation International, 18, 20 - 29. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 095927090800004 X" type="journal article" year="2008">Ryan 2008</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
